blog.description: I have ten thousand fanfic ideas I won't ever write but would love to read, anyone up for the challenge?

summary: Stucky Prompt #4
body:
Stucky Prompt #4

*not my usual Prompt idea but I read a few fics with this and loved them*

Either Bucky or Steve has dissociative identity disorder.

If it’s Bucky, his mind is split between Bucky (before war), Sergeant James Barnes (during the war), and The Assest/Yasha (Winter Soldier).

If it’s Steve, his mind is split between Steve Rogers and Captain America.

*if you write this Prompt please make it accurate to real life DID rather than media DID, or at the very least do enough research where people won’t cringe*

People discuss the latest EndGame trailer…

Meanwhile, the movie will start only on April 29 (!!!😤!!!) where I live so I’m thinking about temporarily logging off all social media starting from April 26. Or maybe even 25th? No way in hell I’ll be able to avoid spoilers otherwise, just no. Nope. Impossible. Tried last year, and how it ended? Got a spoiler RIGHT IN MY FACE about my beloved Bucky getting dusted *shudder*

Yep, it’s decided💪🏻 Although the safest bet must be a return to the very old and very trusty pal Nokia 6300, I swear!

summary:
“Do you trust me?” 
“I do,” Steve replies, without hesitation. Years worth of pain and betrayal evaporating on his tongue. 
I...
body:
“Do you trust me?”

“I do,” Steve replies, without hesitation. Years worth of pain and betrayal evaporating on his tongue.

I never stopped

Steve holds out a hand, almost snatching it back at the last minute. Perhaps it was too much, too much too soon—

Tony nods and grabs hold. His grip is firm, warm, decisive—just as Steve remembers from all those years ago. His eyes twinkle, sparkling with a near-forgotten intensity. He smiles.

“Then let’s go save the goddamn world.”
